<P>I also spent a little time on the User objects..&nbsp; here is low down so far.&nbsp; Your guild members will NOT have forum access, until you give it to them.&nbsp; Giving them access is as easy as clicking a check box next to the people`s names you want to give access to, and clicking the button.&nbsp; I don`t want to give people access without the guildleader/officer giving to them.&nbsp; Now, people will be able to sign up to your forums (non-guildmembers/visitors etc).. they will fill out a form requesting a username/password etc.. and they have to validate their email like the other forums.&nbsp; I am probably going to not allow them to post until you (the guildleader) approves the account... maybe I will set that as an option.</P>
<P>Anyway... a few people have emailed me asking me to make the forums available for use before they are 100% done.. they don`t want to keep using the old forums if the posts are going to not carry over, which is understandable.&nbsp; The only thing I can say, is I will do my best to get it to that point soon.&nbsp; It`s really not that far off, so hopefully I can find a few more hours to do it.</P></font></span>
