											<span id="DataList1__ctl9_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>Custom Rosters now have a configuration setting in their configuration panels to turn off paging for the roster grid.&nbsp; When you turn off paging, your roster will be one long list of everyone in the guild, as opposed to the 35 names per page.&nbsp; This is useful for when you are doing editing on the grid, looking to compare values etc.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Again, this is only on the Custom Roster. To change over to the custom roster, log in as an Admin/Officer account and click the custom roster button that is above the grid.&nbsp; You can switch back and forth between standard and custom roster btw.&nbsp; That was patched a few weeks ago, I dont think I reported it though :)</P>
<P>Still really busy with work, but sneaking in little patches like this here and there.</P></font></span>
